<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories/1.0.0> .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://w3id.org/dpp/access-control> .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> "Annika Moscati" .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> "Bincy Veena" .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> "Peter Johansson" .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/created> "2026-04-01"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date> .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Rahel Kebede" .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "ESPR Annex III-aligned taxonomy of Digital Product Passport data categories.\n         Used as the canonical resource classification for dpp-ac access control\n         policy scoping. Data categories are modelled as OWL classes (not individuals)\n         to enable subsumption-based policy inheritance."@en .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "DPP Data Category Taxonomy"@en .
<http://w3id.org/dpp/data-categories> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "1.0.0" .
